# Cloudflare Pages _headers
# Security headers for static assets served by the CDN edge (bypasses the Worker).
# NOTE: HSTS and CSP are intentionally omitted here — they are set by middleware.ts
# on SSR responses to avoid duplication. The Worker is authoritative for those headers.

# ── Global headers for all static assets ──────────────────────────────────────
/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-origin

# ── COOP/COEP scoped to /workspace/* ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Required for SharedArrayBuffer access (WASM bridge, future Atomics-based workers).
# IMPORTANT: Every asset referenced under /workspace/* must be self-hosted.
# Third-party CDN embeds (scripts, images, iframes) under this path will be blocked
# by COEP unless they carry the `Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: cross-origin` header.
/workspace/*
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-origin
